The removal of FR-1 reason being that this functional requirement is similar to FR-16 as it sends a confirmation letter whereas FR-16 
creates a booking summary, showing time and space allocated to make confirmation of the correct details.

The removal of FR-24 reason being that this functional requirement clashes with FR-16 for the same reasons as FR-1 but does not specify
the summary of the booking and is leaning towards marketing.

The removal of FR-27 reason being that this functional requirement clashes with with FR-21 which already states that when a member is
identified then the discount must be applied on the basis that the booking is not made by a new customer.
